# Kalshi API field reference

When pulling, parsing, archiving, or backtesting **Kalshi API** data, use the generated field catalog as the quick reference — do not guess field names or types.

## Canonical docs

| Artifact | Path |
|----------|------|
| **Field catalog (read first)** | `docs/architecture/KALSHI_API_RESPONSE_FIELDS.md` |
| **Vendor OpenAPI snapshot** | `docs/specs/kalshi_openapi.yaml` |
| **Generator** | `ingest/scripts/generate_kalshi_api_fields_doc.py` |
| **Live spec** | https://docs.kalshi.com/openapi.yaml |
| **WebSocket spec** | `docs/specs/kalshi_asyncapi.yaml` |

KMIA-used endpoints are marked **← KMIA** in the catalog (markets, orderbook, candlesticks, trades, events).

## When to consult

- Adding or changing Kalshi ingest, archive, or backtest parsers
- Mapping API JSON to CSV/JSONL columns
- Debugging missing or renamed fields after API changes
- Writing new scripts that call Kalshi REST endpoints

## Periodic update check

At the **start of any Kalshi API data task** (or when field mismatches appear):

1. Note cached version in `docs/specs/kalshi_openapi.yaml` → `info.version`.
2. Compare to live: `curl -fsSL https://docs.kalshi.com/openapi.yaml | head -20` (or fetch `info.version` only).
3. If versions differ, regenerate:
   ```bash
   python3 ingest/scripts/generate_kalshi_api_fields_doc.py
   ```
4. Scan the diff in `KALSHI_API_RESPONSE_FIELDS.md` for endpoints KMIA uses; update parsers if needed.

**Cadence:** Check on every substantive Kalshi API session; at minimum when the cached spec is >30 days old.

## Parsing notes (from spec)

- Many prices/sizes use fixed-point strings (`*_fp`, `*_dollars`) — see catalog Notes section.
- Orderbook returns **bids only**; YES ask ≈ 100¢ − NO bid.
- WebSocket orderbook fields: `docs/specs/kalshi_asyncapi.yaml` (`orderbook_snapshot`, `orderbook_delta`).
